th theoretical and mathematical foundations of the concept of the Wilson loops in the context of modern quantum field theory, to teach him/her to perform independently some elementary calculations with Wilson lines, and to familiarize him/her with the recent development of the subject in different important areas of research. The target audience of the book consists of graduate and postgraduate students working in various areas of quantum field theory, as well as researchers from other fields.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aGauge fields (Physics). 0aLoops (Group theory). 0aQuantum field theoryvMathematics. 0aQuantum field theoryxMathematics. 4aQuantenfeldtheorie. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Quantum Theory.2bisacsh1 aMertens, Tom, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aVan der Veken, Frederik F., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Studies in Mathematical Physics eBook-Packagez978311064530908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Physical Sciences 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023851808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Physical Sciences 2000 - 2014z9783110637212oZDB-23-GPS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics, Physics 2014z9783110370355oZDB-23-DEM0 cEPUBz97831103829380 cprintz978311030910240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311030921840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110309218423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110309218/original  a978-3-11-023851-8  D